        "answer": "a",
        "explanation": "When the length of an object changes due to the application of force, the ratio of longitudinal stress to longitudinal strain is called Young’s modulus of elasticity. The Young’s modulus of steel is greater than that of rubber; therefore, statement 1 is false. That is why steel is more elastic than rubber. Whereas statement 2 is true, because the extension of a spring is determined by its shear modulus. When the shape of an object changes due to the application of force, the ratio of shear stress to shear strain is called shear modulus.",
