        "explanation": "velocity commensurate with the velocity of the Earth such that it maintain a fixed position in relation to some place on the Earth. When an object moves around the Earth at a speed proportional to the Earth’s motion in such a way that it maintains a fixed distance from a place on the Earth, it is called a geostationary position. Geostationary satellites work on this principle. The orbit of such satellites is circular, and they complete one revolution around the Earth in 24 hours. Since their speed is the same as the Earth’s rotation, these satellites appear stationary. * The time period of a geostationary artificial satellite is —24 hours",
