        "explanation": "A jet engine obtains oxygen from the surroundings and produces thrust, whereas a rocket produces the required thrust by expelling its own stored propellant. For this reason, a jet engine is unsuitable for motion in space, whereas a rocket does not carry oxygen in gaseous form, but in the form of liquid or solid propellants (oxidizer + fuel).",
