        "explanation": "Jet aircraft burn fuel efficiently at the low temperatures of the stratosphere. Also, the atmospheric disturbances caused by convective heating are absent in the stratosphere. Although most weather phenomena such as cloud formation occur in the troposphere, cloud formation has occasionally been observed in the stratosphere and mesosphere as well. There are no vertical winds in the lower part of the stratosphere. Therefore, overall, both statements 1 and 2 are appropriate explanations.",
