        "answer": "b",
        "explanation": "‘Aqua regia’ (Latin: royal water) is a highly powerful oxidizing mixture in which concentrated hydrochloric acid (HCl) and concentrated nitric acid (HNO 3) are generally mixed in the ratio 3:1. This mixture can dissolve chemically inactive metals such as gold and platinum, whereas other acids alone are unable to do so.",
