        "answer": "d",
        "explanation": "The plasma membrane or cell membrane is a semi-permeable living membrane that surrounds the protoplasm of every living cell. According to the concept presented by Robertson (1959), the outer and inner layers of the cell membrane are made of protein, while the middle layer is made of lipid. At present, the concept presented by Singer and Nicolson (1972) regarding the structure of the cell membrane is the most widely accepted. According to this, the cell membrane consists of two layers of phospholipids with certain proteins embedded in between.",
