        "explanation": "Among the classes of food, fats contain the highest amount of calories per gram because, due to their lower oxygen content, their oxidation is greater. The metabolic oxidation of one gram of carbohydrates or protein yields 4.0 kilocalories, whereas the oxidation of one gram of fat yields 9.3 kilocalories of energy. Sources of fats include both animal and plant products. * Which metabolic process yields the maximum energy? – Fats",
        "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 1999"
