        "explanation": "The heart has four chambers through which blood flows. Blood enters the right atrium and passes into the right ventricle. The right ventricle pumps blood to the lungs, where it becomes oxygenated. The oxygenated blood is brought back to the heart by the pulmonary veins, where it enters the left atrium. From the left atrium, blood flows into the left ventricle.",
