        "answer": "",
        "explanation": "Blood is a fluid connective tissue. It keeps moving regularly inside blood vessels to different organs. In the human body, the quantity of blood is about 7 to 8 percent of the body weight. Therefore, in a healthy adult human weighing 70 kilograms, there are about 5 to 6 litres of blood in the body, which is about 1/13th of the total body weight.",
        "source": "U.P. R.O./A.R.O. (Pre) 2017"
