        "answer": "c",
        "explanation": "Blood is a fluid connective tissue, which has two main parts— (i) plasma and (ii) blood corpuscles or formed elements. About 55 percent of the total blood is plasma, while the remaining 45 percent consists of blood corpuscles. Blood corpuscles are of three types—(i) red blood cells, (ii) white blood cells, and (iii) platelets. Therefore, statement (1) is correct. Red blood cells contain a protein called haemoglobin. Haemoglobin transports oxygen. It contains a red-coloured pigment called haem, which gives blood its colour.",
