        "explanation": "The hormone adrenaline, or epinephrine, is secreted by the adrenal medulla. Its secretion increases the heart rate and creates a feeling of excitement in the body. Deficiency of this hormone may make a person feel low-spirited. Such persons are given medicines like cocaine and ephedrine, which stimulate the sympathetic nerve fibres. It is called the ‘fight or flight’ hormone because it helps a person take proper decisions during emergencies and special situations. In this condition, it increases blood pressure and heart rate.",
