        "explanation": "Melatonin is the hormone that regulates sleep and wakefulness. It is secreted only at night. Melatonin is released in small amounts from the pineal gland, located in the human brain between the two ears, and later mixes with the blood. The pineal gland is directly connected with the eyes. Light and darkness have a direct effect on this gland. As evening approaches, the secretion of melatonin begins. Therefore, it is also called the “hormone of night” or the “hormone of darkness.” Normally, it is not secreted in light.",
