        "explanation": "When a disease remains permanently present in a particular area or population, such a situation is called endemic. When an infectious disease spreads rapidly within a short period among a large number of people in a definite population, such a situation is called an epidemic. The spread of an epidemic situation over a large part of the world is called a pandemic.",
        "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) (Re. Exam) 2015"
